Traditional Build & Deployment Workflow 

Puraana tarika kaise tha:-
Developer code likhta tha
Build manually karte the (jar/package banna)
Testing alag team karti thi
Deployment ke liye alag team ko request bhejni padti thi
Sab kuch manual steps se hota tha — slow aur error-prone



2. Waterfall Model in SDLC 

Traditional SDLC ka sabse puraana model:-

Phases: Requirements → Design → Development → Testing → Deployment → Maintenance
Har phase pehle wale ke baad shuru hota tha
Ek baar agla phase shuru ho gaya, peeche jaake change karna mushkil/impossible
"Big Bang" approach — saara software ek saath release hota tha


3. Problems with Traditional SDLC 

purane tarike me kya kya dikkatein thi:-

Slow delivery:                    Months/years lag jaate the ek release me
Late feedback:                    User ke paas product bahut der se pahunchta tha
High risk:                        End me sab kuch test hota tha, bugs late pata chalte the
Difficult to change:              Requirements badalna bahut mushkil tha
Silos (teams alag-alag):          Dev, QA, Ops alag alag kaam karte the, communication gap hota tha
Blame game:                       Kuch gadbad ho to ek dusre par blame karte the
